abtwfUopWLDA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=10&ved=0CF0Q6AEwCQ#v=onepage&q&f=true \"Why We May Wait 20 Years for Ocean Airliners\"] ''Popular Science'', August 1927, p. 9</ref>\n<ref name=\"1GPaH\">U.S. Navy Register, 1930.</ref>\n<ref name=\"zw56a\">The''Admiral Byrd Broadcasts'' ''The Encyclopedia of Old-Time Radio,'' Oxford University Press, 1998, p.5.</ref>\n<ref name=\"QBmaR\">{{Cite news|title = BYRD IS HONORED BY SANTO DOMINGO; Explorer Gets Medal of the Order of Columbus at Ceremony at Republic's Embassy|url = https://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9E00E6D8133FE333A05752C1A9649C946493D6CF|newspaper = The New York Times|date = February 11, 1945|access-date = December 16, 2015|issn = 0362-4331|first = Special To The New York|last = Times}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"SrP7R\">{{Cite news|last=|first=|title=A bordo del Monte Olimpo en Alta Mar|newspaper=[[El Mercurio]]|location=[[Santiago, Chile|Santiago]]|pages=|language=Spanish|publisher=|date=March 5, 1947|url=|accessdate=}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"wVU0G\">Summerhayes & Beeching 2007, p.17</ref>\n<ref name=\"d7E2H\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cd4HTZJUeMM</ref>\n<ref name=\"FSIBZ\">''Byrd Heads Home From Antarctica''. Bernard Kalb. New York Times. February 4, 1956.</ref>\n<ref name=\"ErQBg\">{{Cite news |title=Admiral Byrd Dies at 68. Made 5 Polar Expeditions. Admiral Flew Over Both Poles and Helped Establish Antarctic as a Continent |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1957/03/12/archives/admiral-byrd-dies-at-68-made-5-polar-expeditions-admiral-flew-over.html?sq=Richard+Evelyn+Byrd&scp=7&st=p |quote=5 Arctic and Antarctic Trips Provided Groundwork for U.S. Defense Concepts Frigid Testing Ground First Trip in 1928\u20131929. Born in Virginia. Polar Flight Eclipsed Work Under Federal Auspices. Rear Admiral Richard E. Byrd, U.S.N., retired, the first man to fly over the North and South Poles, died in his sleep tonight at his Brimmer Street home. He was 68 years old. ...|work=New York Times |date= October 9, 1988|a